programme.title: Panorama
programme.desc: In May, BBC reporter Rupert Wingfield-Hayes was expelled from North Korea for allegedly showing disrespect and distorting facts. In this programme, he tells the full story of his visit to the country and explores what his detention and interrogation by senior officials say about this secretive state. He investigates the apparent upturn in the North Korean economy and asks if the signs of improvement in the Capital Pyongyang are real, and also examines if North Koreans are genuinely loyal to leader Kim Jong-un.(n)
